<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFEBFA5ED9FF3B06FE286906" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEBFA5ED9FF3B06FE806E46" blockId="24.[189,310,813,839]" box="[189,310,813,839]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFEBFA5ED9FF3B06FE806E46" bold="true" box="[189,310,813,839]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5ED9FF3B06FE806E46" bold="true" box="[189,310,813,839]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEBFA5ED9FF3B77FE286906" blockId="24.[189,1399,860,1031]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEBFA5ED8173B76FD036E76" authority="Miq. (Tebbit)" box="[341,693,860,887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="teysmanniana">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5ED8173B76FDAE6E77" box="[341,536,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">B. teysmanniana</emphasis>
Miq.(Tebbit)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFEBFA5EDB803B77FC696E76" author="Tebbitt M. C. &amp; Dickson J. H." box="[706,991,860,887]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="112 - 117" refId="ref19028" refString="Tebbitt M. C. &amp; Dickson J. H. 2000. Amended descriptions and revised sectional assignment of some Asian begonias (Begoniaceae). Brittonia 52 (1): 112 - 117. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2666496" type="journal article" year="2000">Tebbitt &amp; Dickson 2000</bibRefCitation>
) in being a lower growing plant (
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5EDC203B76FAC06E77" box="[1378,1398,861,886]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">c.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFEBFA5ED9FF3BAAFEB06E9A" box="[189,262,897,923]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
tall, not 
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5ED82C3BAAFE346E9B" box="[366,386,897,922]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">c.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CADECA6FFEBFA5ED8C83BABFDB76E9A" box="[394,513,896,923]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="70.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="60.0">60–80 cm</quantity>
) with lobed leaves (not entire) having dense red hairs on the leaf veins (not white sparsely puberulent), and differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEBFA5EDB843B8EFB8E6EBE" authority="Miq. (Miquel 1855)" authorityName="Miq. (Miquel" authorityYear="1855" box="[710,1080,932,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5EDB843B8EFCFE6EBE" box="[710,840,933,959]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">B. areolata</emphasis>
Miq. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC43CB2FFEBFA5EDAD43B8EFB866EBE" author="Miquel F. A. W." box="[918,1072,932,959]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref18655" refString="Miquel F. A. W. 1855. Plantae Junghuhnianae. A. W. Sythoff, Lugduni-Batavorum [Leiden]. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 388" type="book" year="1855">Miquel 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having leaves which are smooth above (not densely bullate). 
<taxonomicName id="4C553AC0FFEBFA5EDB293BE1FCE36EE2" authorityName="M. Hughes" authorityYear="2015" box="[619,853,969,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leuserensis">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5EDB293BE1FCE36EE2" box="[619,853,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Begonia leuserensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from both in having 6 (not 5) tepals in the female flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F12C8FFEBFA5ED9FF3C04FE9E699D" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEBFA5ED9FF3C04FEF26948" blockId="24.[189,324,1071,1097]" box="[189,324,1071,1097]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading id="D0A2F62FFFEBFA5ED9FF3C04FEF26948" bold="true" box="[189,324,1071,1097]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9219D51FFEBFA5ED9FF3C04FEF26948" bold="true" box="[189,324,1071,1097]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA4143FFEBFA5ED9FF3C75FE9E699D" blockId="24.[189,1399,1118,1180]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
The epithet is derived from the 
<typeStatus id="54EEFFE1FFEBFA5EDB7A3C74FDDD6978" box="[568,619,1119,1145]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality of Gunung Leuser National Park, to where the species is endemic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
